Day 5 — March 5 — Webhook + Sell Execution Pipeline: @critical
  Goal: Full sell pipeline: QuickNode webhook → dedup → 10-step sell → Jupiter swap → notify.
  T5.1 Hono HTTP Server Setup: @critical
    ☐ Create src/server/index.ts — init Hono app
    ☐ Register POST /webhook/quicknode route
    ☐ Register POST /webhook/telegram route (Grammy webhook)
    ☐ Register GET /health route
    ☐ Register GET /api/waitlist/count route
    ☐ Add global error handler + request logging (Pino)
    ☐ Integrate in src/app.ts: start bot + start Hono on port 3000
    ☐ Webhook mode (prod) vs polling mode (dev) toggle
  T5.2 HMAC-SHA256 Webhook Verification: @critical
    ☐ Extract x-qn-signature, x-qn-timestamp, x-qn-nonce headers
    ☐ Validate timestamp: reject if |now - timestamp| > 30s (invariant 6)
    ☐ Validate nonce: Redis SET NX nonce:{nonce} TTL 60s (replay protection)
    ☐ Compute HMAC-SHA256(secret, timestamp.nonce.body) — timing-safe compare
    ☐ Reject first, process second (invariant 5)
    ☐ Audit log: auth.webhook_reject on any failure
  T5.3 StreamWebhookHandler: @critical
    ☐ Implement dedup: Redis SET NX dedup:{txSignature} TTL 300s
    ☐ Parse webhook payload: tx signature, token mint, buyer, amount
    ☐ Lookup watched-token cache (in-memory Set)
    ☐ Check whitelist: skip if buyer is whitelisted
    ☐ Enqueue to sell-queue via queueService.enqueueSellJob()
    ☐ Always return 200 OK (never 5xx to QuickNode)
    ☐ Build watched-token cache on boot from DB
    ☐ Safety net: refresh cache every CACHE_REFRESH_INTERVAL (60s)
  T5.4 Jupiter API Client: @critical
    ☐ Implement getQuote(inputMint, outputMint, amount, slippageBps)
    ☐ Implement getSwapTransaction(quoteResponse, userPublicKey)
    ☐ Timeout: 15s per request
    ☐ Retry: 1 retry on 5xx with 2s delay
    ☐ Error typing and logging (never log private keys)
  T5.5 Solana Transaction Helpers: @critical
    ☐ Create Connection from config.solana.rpcUrl
    ☐ Implement getTokenBalance(wallet, mint)
    ☐ Implement getSolBalance(wallet)
    ☐ Implement buildCombinedFundingTx (tokens + SOL in 1 TX — the speed optimization)
    ☐ Implement buildSweepAndFeeTx (SOL sweep + fee collection atomic — invariant 18)
    ☐ Implement sendAndConfirmTransaction with `confirmed` commitment (ADR #5)
    ☐ Implement calculateSellAmount(balance, minPct, maxPct) — random in range
  T5.6 SellExecutionWorker (10-Step Pipeline): @critical
    ☐ Step 1: Acquire Redis sell lock (SET NX, TTL 60s) — fail if locked (invariant 14)
    ☐ Step 2: Load project feature config, verify status = watching
    ☐ Step 3: Parallel pre-flight: [getTokenBalance] + [Jupiter getQuote]
    ☐ Step 4: Generate ephemeral wallet (encrypt + store)
    ☐ Step 5: Build + send combined funding TX (tokens + SOL)
    ☐ Step 6: Deserialize Jupiter swap TX, sign with ephemeral, send
    ☐ Step 7: Handle result — success: continue, fail: mark recovery_needed
    ☐ Step 8: Build + send sweep TX (SOL → main wallet) + fee (→ platform wallet)
    ☐ Step 9: Create transaction + fee_ledger records with fee calculations
    ☐ Step 10: Release lock, enqueue notification, check balance=0 → completed
    ☐ Fee calc: gross=sol*1%, discount=10% if referred, tier1=35%, tier2=5%
    ☐ Configure: attempts: 1 (no auto-retry — invariant 16)
    ☐ Ensure sell lock released in finally block (invariant 25)
    ☐ Zero all decrypted keys in finally block

Day 6 — March 6 — Background Workers & Notifications: @critical
  Goal: All 4 BullMQ workers + complete notification system with pinned status.
  T6.1 MarketCapMonitorWorker: @critical
    ☐ Hot loop: poll DexScreener every 30s for all watching features
    ☐ Evaluate MCAP against min_market_cap_usd threshold
    ☐ Below threshold → pause: stop watching, remove from cache, update pinned
    ☐ Above threshold (with 5% hysteresis buffer) → resume watching
    ☐ Cold loop: rebuild watched-token set from DB every 5min, sync to QN KV
    ☐ Redis lock to prevent overlapping cycles (invariant 17)
    ☐ Send state alert notifications on state changes
  T6.2 RecoveryWorker: @critical
    ☐ Run every 5min: scan ephemeral_wallets with status=recovery_needed
    ☐ For each: decrypt key, check balances, attempt sweep
    ☐ Success → status: recovered, Failure → increment recovery_attempts
    ☐ After 5 failures → status: failed + admin notification
    ☐ Zero decrypted keys in finally block
  T6.3 FeePayoutWorker: @high
    ☐ Weekly cron (Sunday): calculate accrued referral earnings
    ☐ Filter: earnings ≥ REFERRAL_MIN_PAYOUT_SOL (0.01)
    ☐ Check payout_wallet_address exists (skip if not set)
    ☐ Execute SOL transfer + record in referral_payouts
    ☐ Send payout notification to each user
    ☐ Below-threshold amounts carry over (invariant 22)
  T6.4 NotificationService: @critical
    ☐ Implement notification consumer (concurrency: 10) from notification-queue
    ☐ Route to type-specific handlers
    ☐ Implement all 8 notification types with correct messages
    ☐ Auto-delete timers: sell=60s, failed=45s, state=30s, payout=never
    ☐ Handle Telegram rate limits with backoff
    ☐ Store timeout refs for graceful shutdown cancellation
  T6.5 Pinned Status Message Lifecycle: @critical
    ☐ Implement 5 states: initial, after-sells, paused, stopped, completed
    ☐ Use ctx.api.editMessageText() to update (never send new)
    ☐ Update stats in project_features.stats JSONB after each sell
    ☐ Handle "message not modified" error gracefully (no-op)
    ☐ Stats persist in DB across bot restarts
  T6.6 Worker Entry Point & Bootstrap: @critical
    ☐ Implement src/worker.ts boot sequence: config → logger → DB → Redis → workers
    ☐ Register: SellExecution (conc:5), Monitor (30s), Recovery (5min), FeePayout (weekly)
    ☐ Implement graceful shutdown: SIGTERM/SIGINT → worker.close() → 30s timeout → exit
    ☐ Implement src/app.ts boot: config → DB → Redis → watched-token cache → bot → Hono
    ☐ Register NotificationConsumer in app process
    ☐ Verify: both processes start and log readiness messages

